  "text": "Extracellular mechanosensors are similar to intracellular systems and rely on mechanical cues to alter cryptic-active sites to open or close under varying degrees of tension or compression. The composition and presentation of the heterogeneous extracellular network of proteins can be quickly modified to change cell behaviour as well as identity [CITATION_1] .",
